    prov1:evidenceText "2014: Ninth French Open title and sustained injuries At the Qatar Open, Nadal won the title beating Gaël Monfils in the final.[250]",
        "Djokovic's Grand Slam debut came at the 2005 Australian Open, followed by his first Slam win at the French Open.[10]: 89–91 That year, he also reached the third round at both Wimbledon[10]: 91 and the US Open, where he beat Gaël Monfils and Mario Ančić.[46]",
        "He began the grass season at the Eastbourne International, winning the title by beating Gaël Monfils—his only tournament win without Vajda until their 2022 split." ;
