<http://example.org/tennis/player/Roger_Federer> a onto:Player ;
    rdfs:label "Roger Federer" ;
    onto:participatedIn <http://example.org/tennis/tournament/Australian_Open>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/tournament/Wimbledon_Championships> ;
    onto:playedAgainst <http://example.org/tennis/player/Andre_Agassi_s>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/player/Andy_Murray>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/player/Anthony_Wilding>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/player/Bjorn_Borg_s>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/player/Cameron_Norrie>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/player/Carlos_Alcaraz>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/player/Dominic_Thiem>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/player/Ernests_Gulbis>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/player/Francisco_Cerundolo>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/player/Jo_Wilfried_Tsonga>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/player/Kei_Nishikori>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/player/Matteo_Berrettini>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/player/Nafal>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/player/Nick_Kyrgios>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/player/Novak_Djokovic>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/player/Rafael_Nadal>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/player/Tommy_Robredo> ;
    onto:won <http://example.org/tennis/tournament/Australian_Open>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/tournament/US_Open>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/tournament/Wimbledon_Championships> ;
    prov1:evidenceText "\"Carlos Alcaraz follows Federer's 2015 path to US Open final, beats Djokovic without dropping a set\".",
        "- \"Federer beats Nadal again\".",
        "- \"Roger Federer beats Rafael Nadal in four sets to reach Wimbledon men's final\".",
        "- The world No. 1 players who Nadal defeated were Roger Federer (13 times)[604] and Novak Djokovic (10 times).[605]",
        "- The world No. 1 players who Nadal has defeated in his career are Roger Federer (13 times) and Novak Djokovic (10 times).[566]",
        "0. Djokovic then claimed his sixth Australian Open, beating Roger Federer in the semifinals and Andy Murray in the final.[179]",
        "At Indian Wells and Miami, he defeated both Federer and Rafael Nadal to claim back-to-back Masters 1000 titles[122]—becoming only the third player to beat both in the same event twice.[123][124]",
        "At Madrid, Nadal beat Federer to become the first man to complete a clean sweep of the three clay-court Masters 1000 titles[164] and it was his 18th Masters title, breaking Andre Agassi's record.[165]",
        "At Monte Carlo, Nadal beat Federer in the final for the third year in a row to become the first player to win four consecutive titles there since Anthony Wilding in 1914.[109]",
        "At Wimbledon, he earned his 100th grass-court win en route to the final,[250] where he defeated Matteo Berrettini to win his sixth title and 20th major, tying Federer and Nadal.",
        "At the ATP Finals, Nadal was defeated by Roger Federer and Jo-Wilfried Tsonga in the round-robin stage, and was eliminated from the tournament.[204]",
        "At the Australian Open, Nadal won his semi-final match against Roger Federer to set up a third successive major final against Novak Djokovic, which he lost in a five-set epic that lasted 5 hours and 53 minutes, the longest Grand Slam final match (by duration) in history.[207]",
        "At the Australian Open, he beat Roger Federer in the semifinals and defeated Dominic Thiem in five sets in the final, earning his eighth Australian Open and 17th Grand Slam title.[226]",
        "At the US Open, Djokovic saved two match points at 4-5 in the fifth set before beating Federer in the semi-finals,[117] but lost to Nadal in the final in four sets.[118]",
        "Djokovic won his second Wimbledon title by defeating Federer in five sets in the final, reclaiming the world No. 1 ranking.[158]",
        "Federer served for the match and had two match points in the US Open semi-finals, but Djokovic won in five sets.[130]",
        "Federer won the final and his fourth consecutive Wimbledon title.[90]",
        "He beat Federer in the semis before losing in straight sets to Djokovic in the final.[249]",
        "He won the Indian Wells Masters, defeating Roger Federer, and the Miami Masters by beating Rafael Nadal.",
        "He won the Italian Open beating Federer in a fifth-set tiebreak in the final, after saving two match points, and equaled Björn Borg's tally of 16 ATP titles won as a teenager.[31]",
        "Nadal beat Federer in the final of the Monte Carlo Masters[82] and Tommy Robredo in the Barcelona final.[83]",
        "Nadal then won consecutive five-set matches during the third and fourth rounds of Wimbledon before being beaten by Federer in a five-set final.",
        "Other matches include the five-set 2013 Australian Open fourth round against Stan Wawrinka,[602][603] the 2018 Wimbledon semifinal against Nadal, which lasted five brutal sets played over two days,[604][605] the five-set 2019 Wimbledon final against Roger Federer, the l" ;
    prov1:sourceURL "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carlos_Alcaraz"^^xsd:anyURI,
        "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Novak_Djokovic"^^xsd:anyURI,
        "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rafael_Nadal"^^xsd:anyURI .

<http://example.org/tennis/tournament/US_Open> a onto:Tournament ;
    rdfs:label "US Open" ;
    onto:hasSurface <http://example.org/tennis/surface/Clay>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/surface/Grass>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/surface/Hard_Court> ;
    prov1:evidenceText "He became the first man to win majors on clay, grass, and hard courts in the same year, and the first to win the French Open, Wimbledon, and the US Open in the same year since Rod Laver in 1969.[178]",
        "He won his 4th hard court title of the year, defeating Djokovic in the US Open final to achieve the Summer Slam and clinch the US Open Series.[245",
        "Jimmy Connors is the only individual to have won US Open singles titles on all three surfaces (grass, clay, and hardcourt), while Chris Evert is the only woman to have won US Open singles titles on two surfaces (clay and hardcourt).[6]" ;
    prov1:sourceURL "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rafael_Nadal"^^xsd:anyURI,
        "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/US_Open_(tennis)"^^xsd:anyURI .

