    prov1:evidenceText "\"Alcaraz fights back to beat Sinner in all-time classic French Open men's final – as it happened\".",
        "\"Alcaraz survives match point to beat Ramos Viñolas in marathon\".",
        "\"Carlos Alcaraz Recently Beat Nadal and Djokovic on Clay.",
        "\"Carlos Alcaraz beats Frances Tiafoe in five-set thriller to reach US Open final\".",
        "\"Carlos Alcaraz follows Federer's 2015 path to US Open final, beats Djokovic without dropping a set\".",
        "\"Carlos Alcaraz sees psychologist in bid to beat Novak Djokovic on Centre Court\".",
        "- \"ATP Finals results 2023: Novak Djokovic beats Carlos Alcaraz to set up Jannik Sinner final\".",
        "- \"Barcelona Open: Carlos Alcaraz beats Stefanos Tsitsipas to retain title\".",
        "- \"Carlos Alcaraz Beats Giulio Zeppieri to Reach Umag Final\".",
        "- \"Carlos Alcaraz beats Alexander Zverev to take Madrid Open title\".",
        "- \"Carlos Alcaraz beats Novak Djokovic to win Wimbledon title in final for the ages\".",
        "- \"Carlos Alcaraz beats Stefanos Tsitsipas in Barcelona Open thriller to guarantee spot in world's top-10\".",
        "- \"Carlos Alcaraz: World number one withdraws from Spain's Davis Cup Finals team\".",
        "- \"China Open: Carlos Alcaraz recovers to beat Jannik Sinner in dramatic final\".",
        "- \"French Open 2025 results: Carlos Alcaraz fights back to beat Jannik Sinner in classic Roland Garros final\".",
        "- \"US Open 2025 results: How Carlos Alcaraz produced 'faultless' performance to beat Jannik Sinner and win title\".",
        "Alcaraz beat top seed Stefanos Tsitsipas in the quarterfinals of the Barcelona Open to enter the world top 10 for the first time on 25 April 2022.[81][82]",
        "Alcaraz comfortably reached the final of the Barcelona Open, where he lost to Holger Rune.",
        "Alcaraz defeated Alexander Zverev in another five-setter to claim his first Roland Garros title.",
        "Alcaraz defeated Félix Auger-Aliassime in the semifinal, making only three unforced errors in the first set.",
        "Alcaraz defeated Jiří Lehečka in the final to claim his third consecutive title, and fifth title of the season.[208]",
        "Alcaraz defeated Pablo Carreño Busta to win the Barcelona title.[85]",
        "Alcaraz defeated world No. 1 Jannik Sinner to claim his first Italian Open title.",
        "Alcaraz easily qualified for the French Open and reached the third round, where he was defeated by Jan-Lennard Struff.",
        "Alcaraz entered the Challenger Oeiras III as an unseeded player, and defeated Facundo Bagnis in the final to claim the fourth Challenger title of his career.[54][55]",
        "Alcaraz made appearances in both seasons of Netflix's Break Point docuseries,[319] and played against Rafael Nadal in The Netflix Slam, a live-streamed tennis match hosted by MGM Resorts International on March 3, 2024.[320]",
        "Alcaraz won their first major final at the French Open, despite Sinner holding three championship points in the fourth set.",
        "As the main draw was postponed due to the COVID-19 pandemic, Alcaraz played the Great Ocean Road Open in early February, where he was defeated by Thiago Monteiro.[46]",
        "As the two-time defending champion at Indian Wells, Alcaraz lost to Jack Draper in the semifinals despite bagelling him in the second set.",
        "At Indian Wells, Alcaraz defeated defending champion Cameron Norrie to reach his first Masters quarterfinal and semifinal, which he lost to Rafael Nadal.[78]",
        "At Wimbledon, Alcaraz lost to Jannik Sinner in the fourth round.[97]",
        "At the French Open, Djokovic defeated world No. 1 Carlos Alcaraz in the semis and beat Casper Ruud in the final to win a record-breaking 23rd major, becoming the first man to achieve a triple Career Grand Slam.[284",
        "At the Queen's Club, Alcaraz claimed his first title on grass in just his third Tour-level grass tournament, beating Alex de Minaur in the final.",
        "At the Vienna Open two weeks later, Alcaraz met Murray for a rematch and defeated him.[68]",
        "Both players met again in the quarterfinals of 2025 Australian Open, in which Djokovic won in four sets[377] and in the semifinals of 2025 US Open, in which Alcaraz won in straight sets.",
        "Carlos Alcaraz defeated four-time defending champion Novak Djokovic in the final, 1–6, 7–6(8–6), 6–1, 3–6, 6–4 to win the gentlemen's singles tennis title at the 2023 Wimbledon Championships.",
        "In 2022, Alcaraz won his first major title at the US Open.",
        "In 2026, Alcaraz won the Australian Open, becoming the youngest man in history to complete the Career Grand Slam, at 22 years, 8 months and 27 days old.",
        "In September 2020, aged 17, Alcaraz played his first qualifying round at a major tournament at the postponed French Open.",
        "In his first main draw match at the Australian Open, Alcaraz defeated fellow qualifier Botic van de Zandschulp in straight sets.",
        "In the first round of Wimbledon, Alcaraz was unexpectedly taken to five sets by Fabio Fognini, who had already announced his retirement and had not won a match all season.[209]",
        "In the second round, Alcaraz was defeated by Mikael Ymer.",
        "In the third round of the US Open, Alcaraz defeated world No. 3 Stefanos Tsitsipas in a dramatic fifth-set tiebreak on Arthur Ashe Stadium.[63]",
        "Notable early matches include the 2022 US Open quarterfinal, which Alcaraz won en route to the title in five sets after saving a match point.[235]",
        "The day after his 19th birthday, Alcaraz defeated five-time champion, world No. 4 and third seed Rafael Nadal in the quarterfinals of the Madrid Open.[86]",
        "The duo soon met for a rematch in the 2023 Wimbledon final, in which Alcaraz defeated four-time defending champion Djokovic in an epic five-setter that lasted 4 hours and 42 minutes.[255]",
        "They had further high profile encounters in the quarterfinals of the 2023 US Open, won by Alcaraz, and the quarterfinals of the 2024 Australian Open, won by Zverev.",
        "They met again at Wimbledon, where Sinner won in four sets, dethroning defending champion Alcaraz; and at the US Open, where Alcaraz won in four sets, dethroning defending champion Sinner.[238]",
        "They would meet again soon after in the 2023 Wimbledon final, in which Alcaraz defeated Djokovic in an epic five-setter that lasted 4 hours and 42 minutes, ending his hopes for the calendar Grand Slam and his decade-long, record 45-match Centre Court win streak.[370]",
        "Two weeks later, at the Miami Open, Alcaraz defeated Casper Ruud to win his first Masters title.",
        "Zverev won the next two sets in a pair of tiebreaks, but Alcaraz recovered in time to win the fifth set, proceeding to his maiden Australian Open final." ;
    prov1:sourceURL "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2023_Wimbledon_Championships_%E2%80%93_Men%27s_singles"^^xsd:anyURI,
        "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carlos_Alcaraz"^^xsd:anyURI,
        "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Novak_Djokovic"^^xsd:anyURI .

<http://example.org/tennis/tournament/Australian_Open> a onto:Tournament ;
    rdfs:label "Australian Open" ;
    onto:hasSurface <http://example.org/tennis/surface/Clay>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/surface/Hard_Court> ;
    prov1:evidenceText "From 2008 to 2019, all of the courts used during the Australian Open were hard courts with Plexicushion acrylic surfaces (though Melbourne Park does have eight practice clay courts which are not used for the tournament)." ;
    prov1:sourceURL "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australian_Open"^^xsd:anyURI .

<http://example.org/tennis/tournament/Wimbledon_Championships> a onto:Tournament ;
    rdfs:label "Wimbledon Championships" ;
    onto:hasSurface <http://example.org/tennis/surface/Clay>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/surface/Grass>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/surface/Hard_Court> ;
    prov1:evidenceText "\"The grass is the star at Wimbledon and this year's Olympic tennis matches\".",
        "\"Wimbledon Drops Grass Court Seeding Formula For 2021 – peRFect Tennis\".",
        "- \"Djokovic Records 100th Grass-Court Match Win, Reaches Wimbledon Semi-finals\".",
        "- \"Wimbledon grass\".",
        "As a result of the COVID-19 global pandemic, the All England Club announced on 1 April 2020 that the entire grass-court season was to be cancelled as a public safety precaution until June 2021, marking the first time a Wimbledon tournament would not be played since World War II.[30]",
        "As of 2011, early training occurs at the Wimbledon All England Lawn Tennis Club Community Centre, before moving to the Wimbledon All England Lawn Tennis Club Covered Courts, to the side of the Grounds, and then to outside courts (8, 9, 10) the week before the Championships to ensure that BBGs gain a feel of the grass court.[citation needed]",
        "At Wimbledon, he earned his 100th grass-court win en route to the final,[250] where he defeated Matteo Berrettini to win his sixth title and 20th major, tying Federer and Nadal.",
        "Djokovic reached the final of the Gerry Weber Open on grass but lost to Tommy Haas, and then suffered another defeat to Haas in the quarterfinals of Wimbledon.[101][102]",
        "He also ended Federer's streak of five consecutive Wimbledon titles and 65 straight wins on grass courts.[121]",
        "He became the first man to win majors on clay, grass, and hard courts in the same year, and the first to win the French Open, Wimbledon, and the US Open in the same year since Rod Laver in 1969.[178]",
        "Nadal became the world No. 1 for the first time in 2008 after defeating Federer in a historic Wimbledon final, his first major championship off clay, which he followed with an Olympic singles gold at the 2008 Beijing Olympics.",
        "Nadal went on to win the 2015 Mercedes Cup against Serbian Viktor Troicki, his first grass court title since he won at Wimbledon in 2010.[272]",
        "On grass, he fell to Nadal in the Queen's Club final,[82] and suffered a second-round loss at Wimbledon to Marat Safin, ending a streak of five straight major semifinals.[83]",
        "Other grass-court tournaments before Wimbledon are Eastbourne, Great Britain, and Rosmalen in the Netherlands, both combining mixed events.",
        "The Australian and the US tournaments are played on hard courts, the French on clay court, and Wimbledon on grass court.",
        "The LTA was given the perpetual right to organize the World Grass Court Championships, to be held at Wimbledon, and France received permission to stage the World Hard Court Championships until 1916.[11]",
        "The only grass-court tournament scheduled after the Championships is the Hall of Fame Tennis Championships at Newport, Rhode Island, USA, which takes place the week after Wimbledon.",
        "These tournaments are held clay and grass courts, respectively, surfaces very different from each other,[71] usually being held a few weeks from each other,[185] meaning that players who have deep runs in the French Open have little time to adapt to the different surface conditions found at Wimbledon.[186][187]" ;
    prov1:sourceURL "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grand_Slam_(tennis)"^^xsd:anyURI,
        "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Novak_Djokovic"^^xsd:anyURI,
        "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rafael_Nadal"^^xsd:anyURI,
        "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wimbledon_Championships"^^xsd:anyURI .

<http://example.org/tennis/tournament/French_Open> a onto:Tournament ;
    rdfs:label "French Open" ;
    onto:hasSurface <http://example.org/tennis/surface/Clay>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/surface/Grass>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/surface/Hard_Court> ;
    prov1:evidenceText "\"French Open Adds Day; Clay Stays the Same\".",
        "\"Nadal Embraces History With a Record Seventh Title on the Clay of Roland Garros\".",
        "- \"Why is the French Open played on clay?\". 19 May 2022.",
        "He became the first man to win majors on clay, grass, and hard courts in the same year, and the first to win the French Open, Wimbledon, and the US Open in the same year since Rod Laver in 1969.[178]",
        "He became the third man to win every modern big title on clay (French Open, Monte-Carlo, Madrid, and Rome) after Rafael Nadal and Novak Djokovic.[197]",
        "He continued his good form on clay at the French Open by reaching the final without dropping a set in the first five rounds, including a quarterfinal clash with Nadal and a five-set semifinal victory over Andy Murray which took two days to complete.",
        "He is also the player with the most victories over Nadal on clay, having defeated him twice at the French Open and all three clay court Masters events, notably at the 2013 Monte-Carlo Masters, where he ended Nadal's run of eight consecutive titles.",
        "However, Nadal retained his No. 1 ranking during the clay-court season and won his sixth French Open title by defeating Roger Federer.[196]",
        "In 2019, former world No. 1 and 1995 French Open champion Thomas Muster stated: \"Rafael Nadal is the best clay-court player ever\".[426]",
        "It was open to all amateurs and since 1928 has been held on clay courts at the Stade Roland-Garros in Paris, France.[66][69]",
        "Nadal holds the men's all-time records for the most majors won without losing a set (4), the most match wins at a single major (112 at the French Open), and the highest match-winning percentage at clay court majors (96.6%), among many others.",
        "Nadal then broke Argentinian Guillermo Vilas's 29-year male record of 53 consecutive clay-court match victories by beating Robin Söderling in the first round of the French Open.[85][86]",
        "Organized by the Fédération française de tennis (FFT), formerly known as the Fédération Française de Lawn Tennis until 1976,[70] the French Open is the only Grand Slam tournament played on a red clay surface.[71]",
        "The World Hard Court Championships was considered the premier clay championship in France from 1912–1923 (apart from one year held in Belgium) as it admitted international competitors, and it is therefore often seen as the true precursor to the French Open before 1925.[14][74]",
        "These tournaments are held clay and grass courts, respectively, surfaces very different from each other,[71] usually being held a few weeks from each other,[185] meaning that players who have deep runs in the French Open have little time to adapt to the different surface conditions found at Wimbledon.[186][187]" ;
    prov1:sourceURL "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carlos_Alcaraz"^^xsd:anyURI,
        "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/French_Open"^^xsd:anyURI,
        "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grand_Slam_(tennis)"^^xsd:anyURI,
        "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Novak_Djokovic"^^xsd:anyURI,
        "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rafael_Nadal"^^xsd:anyURI .

