        "- \"Nadal beats Djokovic in late-night Paris thriller\".",
        "- \"Nadal beats Djokovic to help Spain clinch win\".",
        "- \"Nadal beats Federer for 18th Masters title\".",
        "- \"Nadal beats Federer in Abu Dhabi final\".",
        "- \"Nadal beats Federer in Monte Carlo final\".",
        "- \"Nadal beats Ferrer for 7th Barcelona Open win\".",
        "- \"Nadal beats Ferrer for record 8th French Open win\".",
        "- \"Nadal beats Hajek for 4–0 Spain lead in final\".",
        "- \"Nadal beats Medvedev in Melbourne classic\".",
        "- \"Nadal beats Robredo i",
        "- \"Nadal withdraws from Paris and London tournaments\".",
        "- \"Rafael Nadal Beats Dominic Thiem To Win Mutua Madrid Open Title | ATP Tour | Tennis\".",
        "- \"Rafael Nadal Saves M.P., Beats Stefanos Tsitsipas For 12th Barcelona Title | ATP Tour | Tennis\". ATP Tour.",
        "- \"Rafael Nadal Withdraws From Indian Wells & Miami\".",
        "- \"Rafael Nadal beaten by Taylor Fritz in Indian Wells final\".",
        "- \"Rafael Nadal beats Daniil Medvedev to win US Open men's final – as it happened\".",
        "- \"Rafael Nadal beats David Ferrer to claim a fifth Rome Masters\".",
        "- \"Rafael Nadal beats David Ferrer to win Mexican Open title in Acapulco\".",
        "- \"Rafael Nadal beats Gael Monfils to win Qatar title\".",
        "- \"Rafael Nadal beats John Isner to win Cincinnati Open\".",
        "- \"Rafael Nadal beats Novak Djokovic in straight sets at Rome Masters\".",
        "- \"Rafael Nadal beats Novak Djokovic to win record seventh French Open title\".",
        "- \"Rafael Nadal beats Roger Federer to win Madrid Masters\".",
        "- \"Rafael Nadal wins battle of generations to beat Alcaraz, 18, to Indian Wells final\".",
        "- \"US Open 2019: Rafael Nadal beats Daniil Medvedev to win 19th Grand Slam title\".",
        "- \"Wimbledon 2015: Rafael Nadal beaten by Dustin Brown\".",
        "- The world No. 1 players who Nadal defeated were Roger Federer (13 times)[604] and Novak Djokovic (10 times).[605]",
        "- The world No. 1 players who Nadal has defeated in his career are Roger Federer (13 times) and Novak Djokovic (10 times).[566]",
        "2012: Seventh French Open title At Qatar Open, Nadal lost to Gaël Monfils in the semi-finals.[206]",
        "2014: Ninth French Open title and sustained injuries At the Qatar Open, Nadal won the title beating Gaël Monfils in the final.[250]",
        "After recovering from an eye infection at the Dubai Championships, he won his fifth Indian Wells Masters title, beating Nadal and Milos Raonic.",
        "Aged 12, Nadal began attending the Balearic Islands training centre 50 kilometers away from Manacor in Palma.[7]",
        "Around the time he won the 2012 French Open, Nadal acquired a vacation home, a two-storey villa in Playa Nueva Romana, in the Dominican Republic, for about 2 million euros.[554]",
        "As a warm-up ahead of Wimbledon, Nadal played in Halle, losing to Philipp Kohlschreiber in the quarterfinals.[223]",
        "At 4 hours and 48 minutes, they played the longest final (in terms of time on court, surpassed in 2019) in Wimbledon history, and because of rain delays, Nadal won the fifth set 9–7 in near-darkness.",
        "At Australian Open, Nadal progressed to his fifth Australian Open final without losing a set, then won only eight games against Novak Djokovic, which was Nadal's first straight-sets defeat in a major final.[311]",
        "At Indian Wells, Nadal won his 13th Masters tournament, beating Andy Murray.[137]",
        "At Madrid, Nadal beat Federer to become the first man to complete a clean sweep of the three clay-court Masters 1000 titles[164] and it was his 18th Masters title, breaking Andre Agassi's record.[165]",
        "At Madrid, Nadal lost to Fernando Verdasco, whom he held a 13–0 record against.",
        "At Monte Carlo, Nadal beat Djokovic in the final to win a record fifth consecutive singles title.[138]",
        "At Monte Carlo, Nadal beat Federer in the final for the third year in a row to become the first player to win four consecutive titles there since Anthony Wilding in 1914.[109]",
        "At Rotterdam, Nadal sustained a knee injury during the final, which he lost to Andy Murray.[134]",
        "At Umag, Nadal lost to Moyá in the semi-finals.",
        "At Wimbledon, Djokovic won a five-hour quarterfinal over Marcos Baghdatis before retiring in the semifinals against Nadal due to elbow issues.[65][66]",
        "At Wimbledon, Nadal beat Juan Martín del Potro in five sets in the quarters.",
        "At Wimbledon, Nadal beat No. 20 Andre Agassi in Agassi's last ever match at Wimbledon.[89]",
        "At the ATP Finals, Nadal beat Tsitsipas and Medvedev in the round-robin stage, but failed to progress to the semi-finals.[324]",
        "At the ATP Finals, Nadal defeated Rublev and defending champion Tsitsipas progressing to the semi-finals and securing ending the year as No. 2.[338]",
        "At the ATP Finals, Nadal was defeated by Roger Federer and Jo-Wilfried Tsonga in the round-robin stage, and was eliminated from the tournament.[204]",
        "At the Australian Open Nadal won his first three matches in straight sets against Hugo Dellien, Federico Delbonis and Pablo Carreño Busta.",
        "At the Australian Open, Nadal beat Fernando Verdasco in the semis in the fifth-longest match in Australian Open history (5 hours 14 minutes).[130][131]",
        "At the Australian Open, Nadal won his semi-final match against Roger Federer to set up a third successive major final against Novak Djokovic, which he lost in a five-set epic that lasted 5 hours and 53 minutes, the longest Grand Slam final match (by duration) in history.[207]",
        "At the Brasil Open, Nadal beat David Nalbandian in the final.[230]",
        "At the French Open, Nadal beat Kei Nishikori and Roger Federer (their first meeting at the tournament since 2011) en route to the final, dropping only one set en route.",
        "At the French Open, Nadal beat Söderling in the final to win his fifth French Open.",
        "At the French Open, Nadal won his 17th Grand Slam title.",
        "At the French Open, Nadal won his semi-final match against Ferrer to set up another final against Novak Djokovic.",
        "At the French Open, he beat Nadal in a four-set semifinal and came from two sets down to defeat Tsitsipas in the final.[245]",
        "At the US Open Nadal advanced to the fourth round but was defeated by 24th seed Lucas Pouille in 5 sets.",
        "At the US Open, Nadal lost one set (against Marin Čilić) en route to the final, where he beat Medvedev in five sets to win his fourth US Open title and 19th major title overall, and completed his second-best Grand Slam year.[322]",
        "At the US Open, Nadal lost to defending champion Andy Roddick in the second round.[36]",
        "At the inaugural ATP Cup Nadal helped Spain reach the final where they lost to Serbia, with Nadal losing to Djokovic in straight sets.[329]",
        "Between Barcelona and Rome, Nadal beat Federer in the \"Battle of Surfaces\" exhibition match in Mallorca, with the court being half grass and half clay.[98][99]",
        "Career Nadal won the Spanish junior championships in 1997 and 1998, beating Ricardo Villacorta and Marcel Granollers respectively.[16][17]",
        "During the Majorca flood in October 2018, Nadal, who was recovering from injury at home in Majorca, opened his tennis academy centre to the victims.[495]",
        "Following Nadal's withdrawal from the Paris Masters, Djokovic regained the No. 1 ranking, but lost to unseeded Karen Khachanov in the final.",
        "Following his Wimbledon loss, Nadal won 16 consecutive matches and three consecutive tournaments, the Swedish Open, Stuttgart Open, and the Canada Masters, defeating Agassi in the final of the latter to win the first hardcourt title of his career and to bring his ranking to No. 2 on 25 July 2005, where he remained for the next three years behind Roger Federer.[36]",
        "However, Nadal retained his No. 1 ranking during the clay-court season and won his sixth French Open title by defeating Roger Federer.[196]",
        "In 2000, Nadal dominated the U14 circuit, winning Les Petits As in Tarbes, beating Julien Gely in the final,[16][23][24] and the European Junior Masters in Prato.[16][25]",
        "In December, Nadal beat Tomáš Berdych in the Davis Cup final.[156]",
        "In January, Nadal won Melbourne Summer Set 1, beating Maxime Cressy in the final.",
        "In July, Nadal beat Stan Wawrinka in the final of the clay-court Stuttgart Open.[101]",
        "In July, Nadal won the U14 Spanish championships, beating his friend and training partner Tomeu Salvá in the final,[16][28] despite breaking a finger on his left hand during the first round.[28][29]",
        "In March, Nadal beat Janko Tipsarević and Novak Djokovic to help Spain beat Serbia in Davis Cup round one.[135][136]",
        "In Miami, he defeated Rafael Nadal in the quarterfinals, Andy Murray in the semifinals, and Guillermo Cañas in the final, earning his first Masters title and becoming the youngest male champion in the history of the tournament.[52]",
        "In October, Nadal defeated No. 76 Albert Montañés in the quarterfinals of a Challenger at Barcelona,[16] before losing to Albert Portas in the semi-finals.[45]",
        "In September, Nadal entered the final Challenger event of his career, on hard courts in Saint-Jean-de-Luz, retiring with an injury against Richard Gasquet, who never defeated Nadal again.[48][56]",
        "In late 1998, Nadal won the season-ending U12 Junior Masters at Stuttgart, beating future world No. 5 Kevin Anderson in the final.[19]",
        "In response to the 2010 Haiti earthquake, Nadal played in a special charity event alongside fellow top tennis players during the 2010 Australian Open called Hit for Haiti, with proceeds going to Haiti earthquake victims.[492]",
        "In the 2004 Davis Cup final, 18-year-old Nadal beat world No. 2 Andy Roddick on clay in Spain to help his nation clinch the title over the United States.",
        "In the Mexican Open, Nadal defeated David Ferrer, losing just two games.[231]",
        "In the quarterfinals, Nadal was hampered by burns to his right hand after an accident at a Japanese restaurant and lost to Mardy Fish in straight sets.[200] After d",
        "In the second-longest Wimbledon semifinal to date, Djokovic beat Nadal in five sets played over two days.[204]",
        "In the third round of the 2015 US Open, Nadal again lost to Fognini, despite an early two set lead.[275]",
        "In their first Grand Slam final at the 2010 US Open, Nadal beat Djokovic in four sets, achieving the career Grand Slam.[395]",
        "Joachim Johansson, ranked No. 690, upset Nadal in the second round of the Stockholm Open[92] and he lost to Tomáš Berdych in the quarterfinals of the Madrid Masters.",
        "La Décima, third US Open title, year-end No. 1 At the Brisbane International Nadal lost to Milos Raonic in the quarterfinals.[289]",
        "Later that year, Nadal defeated Djokovic in the US Open final to complete the Summer Slam.[393]",
        "Nadal beat Federer in a five-set final (their first meeting in a hard-court major) to win his first hard-court major singles title,[132] and was the first Spaniard to win the Australian Open.[133]",
        "Nadal beat Federer in the final of the Monte Carlo Masters[82] and Tommy Robredo in the Barcelona final.[83]",
        "Nadal beat Novak Djokovic in the quarterfinals, the first-ever meeting of their historic rivalry.[87]",
        "Nadal beat Stan Wawrinka to win a record tenth French Open title.",
        "Nadal defeated Novak Djokovic in the Men's Singles French Open final to win his 9th French Open title and a 5th straight win.",
        "Nadal dropped only one set at the event, beating Dominic Thiem in the final in three sets.[307]",
        "Nadal extended his streak by winning the China Open, beating Nick Kyrgios.[297]",
        "Nadal extended his winning streak to a career-best 32 matches by winning his second Canada Masters title in Toronto, and reaching the semi-finals at Cincinnati, where he lost to Djokovic.[122]",
        "Nadal had a rib injury and lost to Taylor Fritz in straight sets in the final.[352]",
        "Nadal helped Spain secure a Davis Cup World Group place for 2014, beating Sergiy Stakhovsky and winning a doubles with Marc Lopez.",
        "Nadal holds the men's all-time records for the most majors won without losing a set (4), the most match wins at a single major (112 at the French Open), and the highest match-winning percentage at clay court majors (96.6%), among many others.",
        "Nadal lost to Djokovic in the quarterfinals of the French Open, ending his winning streak of 39 consecutive victories in Paris since his 2009 defeat by Robin Söderling.[271]",
        "Nadal lost to Federer in the fourth round at Indian Wells and the Miami final.[290",
        "Nadal next played at Monte Carlo and reached the quarterfinals, where he lost to Andrey Rublev in three sets.[342]",
        "Nadal qualified for the semi-finals, where he lost to Federer.",
        "Nadal reached his fifth Challenger final of the year in Aix-en-Provence, which he lost to Mariano Puerta.[48]",
        "Nadal reached the final of the Japan Open, where he was defeated by Andy Murray.[203]",
        "Nadal retired from the sport after playing for Spain in the 2024 Davis Cup Finals.",
        "Nadal then beat David Ferrer in a three-set final to clinch his seventh title in eight years at Barcelona.[217]",
        "Nadal then broke Argentinian Guillermo Vilas's 29-year male record of 53 consecutive clay-court match victories by beating Robin Söderling in the first round of the French Open.[85][86]",
        "Nadal then overtook him when he beat Federer for his 7th title at the Italian Open.[236]",
        "Nadal then reached the semi-finals of both the Indian Wells, where he was beaten by Federer, and Miami, where he withdrew because of knee problems.[214",
        "Nadal then won consecutive five-set matches during the third and fourth rounds of Wimbledon before being beaten by Federer in a five-set final.",
        "Nadal was beaten by Djokovic in straight sets in Monte Carlo to end his eight-year reign at the tournament.[233]",
        "Nadal went on to win the 2015 Mercedes Cup against Serbian Viktor Troicki, his first grass court title since he won at Wimbledon in 2010.[272]",
        "Nadal withdrew from Indian Wells and Miami to recover from his Australian Open injury and didn't play on tour again in 2023.[366]",
        "Nadal won 92 ATP Tour singles titles, with 22 major titles—including a record 14 French Open titles—as well as 36 Masters titles and an Olympic gold medal.",
        "Nadal won his 11th Monte Carlo title without losing a set (beating Kei Nishikori in the final, a then-record-breaking 31st Masters title).[302",
        "Nadal won his 13th French Open, beating Novak Djokovic in straight sets in the final, only losing seven games.",
        "Nadal won in four sets against Thiem to claim his record-extending twelfth French Open title.[317]",
        "Nadal won six of the nine, losing the first two Wimbledon finals and 2017 in Australia.",
        "Nadal won the French Open beating David Ferrer in the final, breaking the record for the most match wins in the tournament with his 59th victory.[237]",
        "Nadal won the Japan Open after beating Gaël Monfils in the final for his seventh title of the season.[181]",
        "Nadal won two of his three-round robin matches to advance to the semi-finals of the Tennis Masters Cup in Shanghai, where Federer defeated him in straight sets.[106]",
        "Olympic doubles gold Nadal lost to Djokovic in straight sets in the final in Doha.",
        "On 10 October 2024, Nadal stated his intention to retire from the sport after playing for Spain in the Davis Cup Finals in Málaga, Spain, in November.[372][373][374]",
        "On clay, he defeated Richard Gasquet in the final of the Estoril Open,[60] and reached the quarterfinals in Rome and Hamburg, losing to Nadal and Carlos Moyá, respectively.[61][62]",
        "On his 19th birthday, Nadal defeated Federer in the French Open semi-finals, being one of only four players to defeat him that year.",
        "On the day he turned 14, Nadal won the Sport Goofy Trophy in Getxo, beating Granollers in the final.[26][27]",
        "On the other hand, notable players who have won multiple Grand Slam events and have won the French Open, includes Rafael Nadal, Björn Borg, Steffi Graf, Ivan Lendl, Monica Seles, Novak Djokovic, Mats Wilander, Serena Williams, Stan Wawrinka, Justine Henin and Chris Evert, showing proof of their great versatility.",
        "Other matches include the five-set 2013 Australian Open fourth round against Stan Wawrinka,[602][603] the 2018 Wimbledon semifinal against Nadal, which lasted five brutal sets played over two days,[604][605] the five-set 2019 Wimbledon final against Roger Federer, the l",
        "Rafael Nadal defeated Casper Ruud in the final, 6–3, 6–3, 6–0 to win the men's singles tennis title at the 2022 French Open.",
        "Three days later, Nadal's 24-match winning streak was snapped in the first round on grass at Halle, Germany, where he lost to No. 147 Alexander Waske.[72]",
        "major main draw debut in Wimbledon, Nadal defeated Mario Ančić, and reached the third round to become the youngest man to do so since Boris Becker in 1984.[31][52]" ;
